On Saturday, the Minister of Foreign Affairs of North Korea informed the United Nations that the continuation of sanctions would deepen his confidence in the United States and that there was no possibility that his country would give up nuclear weapons unilaterally under those circumstances.
Ri Yong Ho declared before the annual General Assembly of the international body that North Korea had taken " important measures of good will" over the past year, such as stopping nuclear and missile testing, disarming nuclear testing facilities, and commiting itself to the non-proliferation of nuclear weapons and nuclear technology.
